# Public display typography

Text on the **venue / TV display** (`apps/display/**`) must stay legible from across a room. Pick the tier that matches **where** the text lives:

| Tier | When | CSS utility / token |
|------|------|---------------------|
| **Primary** | Full-viewport headlines (spotlight question, pairing title, page H1) | `DISPLAY_TEXT_PRIMARY` → `clamp(5vh, 10vh, 12vh)` |
| **Headline** | Venue mosaic question / countdown strip (shares row with chips) | `DISPLAY_TEXT_HEADLINE` → `clamp(4vh, 6.5vh, 9vh)` |
| **Secondary** | Full-viewport subtitles, metadata, dock labels | `DISPLAY_TEXT_SECONDARY` → `≥ 5vh` |
| **Primary CQ** | Primary copy inside an `@container` cell (~7cqh of the cell) | `DISPLAY_TEXT_PRIMARY_CQ` |
| **Secondary CQ** | Secondary copy inside an `@container` cell | `DISPLAY_TEXT_SECONDARY_CQ` |
| **Primary/Secondary CQW** | Copy that should track cell **width** (community cards, pot numerals) | `DISPLAY_TEXT_PRIMARY_CQW` / `DISPLAY_TEXT_SECONDARY_CQW` |
| **Badge CQ** | Seat markers, compact numerals on felts | `DISPLAY_TEXT_BADGE_CQ` |
| **Dense CQ** | Multi-row lists (gutter rosters, welcome tips) | `DISPLAY_TEXT_DENSE_CQ` |

## Critical rule: never mix `vh` into `@container` cells

```css
/* ❌ BAD — 5vh wins in small mosaic tiles; everything becomes viewport-sized */
font-size: max(5vh, 10cqh);

/* ✅ GOOD — scale to the cell only */
font-size: clamp(3.5cqh, 7cqh, 11cqh);
```

- Put `@container` / `@container/size` on the cell wrapper, then use `*_CQ` / `*_CQW` / `DENSE_CQ` inside.
- Do **not** use `DISPLAY_TEXT_PRIMARY` or `DISPLAY_TEXT_SECONDARY` (`vh`) inside mosaic tiles, seating cards, gutter rosters, or welcome-wall panels.

## Checklist before merging display UI changes

- [ ] Full-screen bands use `PRIMARY` / `HEADLINE` / `SECONDARY` (`vh`).
- [ ] Tile, panel, roster, and felt copy use `*_CQ`, `*_CQW`, `BADGE_CQ`, or `DENSE_CQ` only.
- [ ] No `max(5vh, …cqh)` or `min-h-[max(5vh,…)]` on container-scoped elements.
- [ ] No Tailwind `text-xs` / `text-sm` / fixed px for legible display copy.
